/**
*  Stateless Investment Proposal Generation.
*  This stateless endpoint creates an investment proposal given a portfolio using client-specific guideline. The request
*  requires an aggregate object representing a parent entity. which can be a single portfolio or a collection of portfolios.
*  Optionaloptimization parameters,such as optimization reason and buy list, and anlysis settings, such as sleeve
*  information and wealth projection settings, are also accepted. The endpoint returns the original portfolio, the proposed
*  portfolio, a list of changes and optionally, the proposal analysis. This API is staeless; it does not persist any generated
*  propsals or their anlysis within Aladdin Wealth.
*
*
*QUERY PARAMETERS
* includeAnalysis: boolean
*  A true/false flag to indicate if as part of the request the proposal should be analyzed and
*  the analysis should be included as part of the response Defaults to false.
*
*  analytics: Array of strings
*  Items Enum: "PORTFOLIO","CUSTOM","COMMENTS","TAX","RULES","SCORES","STATUS","CHANGES","ALL"
*  The analytics to include in the response, in comma-separated format. Defaults to ALL.
*
*date  string<date>
*  An ISO-8601 formatted string representing the date when the proposal should be analyzed as of in UTC
*
* HEADER PARAMETERS
*  VND.com.blackrock.Request-ID     string<uuid>
*  Unique identifier assigned by client program to a request, to aid support
*  and debugging. Aladdin will echo it back in response. UUID(4) recommended.
*
*  VND.com.blackrock.Origin-Timestamp  string<imf-fixdate>
*  Timestamp assigned at the origin of this request, in "HTTP-date" format
*  as defined by RFC 7231 (IMF-fixdate format/UTC)
*
*  REQUEST BODY SCHEMA   application/json
*  A GenerateProposalRequest
*
*  id: string
*  An optional identifier that will be applied to the generated Proposal for
*  tracking. Must be unique. If not provided, a randomly-generated UUID
*  identifier will be assigned to the gerated Proposal.
*
*  reason: string
*
*  aggregate: object(AggregateComposition)
*  Representation for a aggregate collection of investment portfolios
*
*  parameters: object
*  Key vlaue pairs of arbitrary form field parameters
*
*  buyList: Array of objects (BuyListItem)
*  List of potential positions to be evaluated for purchase
*
*  sleeveTags: Array of strings
*  List of unique dynamic sleeve tags contained within aggregate or individual portfolios
*
*  simulatedPerformanceUserInputs: object(SimulatedPerformanceUserInputs)
*  Override fee value for calculating netSimulatedPerformance.
*
*
*
*
*
*
*
*
*
*
**/



